            <title>[LU-2691] Interop 2.1.4&lt;-&gt;2.4 failure on test suite sanity test_24u: error on ioctl 0x4008669a for &apos;/mnt/lustre/f.sanity.24u&apos; (3): No data available</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-2691</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;This issue was created by maloo for sarah &amp;lt;sarah@whamcloud.com&amp;gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This issue relates to the following test suite run: &lt;a href=&quot;https://maloo.whamcloud.com/test_sets/9e665c02-6472-11e2-bfb2-52540035b04c&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://maloo.whamcloud.com/test_sets/9e665c02-6472-11e2-bfb2-52540035b04c&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The sub-test test_24u failed with the following error:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;== sanity test 24u: create stripe file == 17:40:26 (1358818826)&lt;br/&gt;
error on ioctl 0x4008669a for &apos;/mnt/lustre/f.sanity.24u&apos; (3): No data available&lt;br/&gt;
write: Bad file descriptor&lt;br/&gt;
 sanity test_24u: @@@@@@ FAIL:  &lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;
</description>
                <environment>server: 2.1.4 RHEL6&lt;br/&gt;
client: lustre-master build #1176</environment>
